    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="How-to-share-a-secret-s"><a href="#How-to-share-a-secret-s" class="headerlink" title="How to share a secret s?"></a>How to share a secret <em>s</em>?</h1><h2 id="问题描述"><a href="#问题描述" class="headerlink" title="问题描述"></a>问题描述</h2><p>怎样把s分成n份，使得任意不少于t份组合，能恢复出s？</p><h3 id="缘起"><a href="#缘起" class="headerlink" title="缘起"></a>缘起</h3><p>《组合数学》（Chung Laung Liu，刘炯朗，台湾清华大学校长）中的一个数学问题：</p><blockquote><p>Eleven scientists are working on a secret project. They wish to lock up the documents in a cabinet so that the cabinet can be opened if and only if six or more of the scientists are present. What is the smallest number of locks needed? What is the smallest number of keys to the locks each scientist must carry?</p></blockquote><h4 id="Problem-Description"><a href="#Problem-Description" class="headerlink" title="Problem Description"></a>Problem Description</h4><p>The whole set is U (|U|=m), divided into 11 subsets and each is of size n, s.t. only the union of any six or more sub-sests can recover the whole set U. Give m,n.</p><h4 id="Solution"><a href="#Solution" class="headerlink" title="Solution"></a>Solution</h4><p>1)Any less than six set will not know at least one element in U.</p>]]></content>
    
